<DOC><DOCNO> AP891212-0059 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-12-89 1118EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Romania-Border     12-12 0125</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Romania-Border,0129</SECOND><HEAD>Border Guards Placed Under Police Control</HEAD><DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Romania's hard-line Communist leadershiphas put its border guards under police supervision, the Romanianstate news agency reported today.   Agerpres gave few details but it appeared the move was meant tostop the growing number of illegal crossings by citizens fleeingpolitical repression and economic hardship.   Former Olympic gymnast Nadia Comaneci defected on Nov. 30 andnow is in the United States.   The Communist Party's ruling Politburo met Monday and decided totransfer border guard units from the Ministry of National Defense``to the subordination of the Ministry of the Interior,'' Agerpressaid.   Other Romanians who fled across the border into Hungary recentlyincluded eight shepherds and their herd of 1,140 sheep.</TEXT></DOC>